"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820758","Cabinet Office","false","2018-01-16","<p>Our priority is to keep public services running. We have extensive contingency plans and are working hard to minimise any disruption.</p><p> </p><p>We have worked closely across government with all affected departments and stakeholders to develop robust contingency plans that enable us to maintain the continuity and mitigate impacts to public services where possible. It would not be appropriate to speculate on commercially sensitive discussions at this time.</p><p> </p><p>As these plans contain commercially sensitive information it would not be appropriate to publish them.</p><p> </p><p>We will of course keep the House updated on developments as they arise.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820758/answer",,,,,"122169 ; 122170 ; 122171 ; 122175","2018-01-16T17:40:01.157Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820758/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820758/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-01-11","Carillion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, pursuant to the oral contribution of the Parliamentary Secretary of 10 January 2018, Official Report, cols. 307-8, on Government Contracts: SMEs, who was consulted in the preparation of the Carillion contingency plans.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","122176"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820759","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-01-19","<p>Candidates for the Legal Trustee Role, which was advertised in the most recent round of appointments to the board of the Charity Commission, were assessed against the following selection criteria which were published on the Centre for Public Appointments website when the vacancy was advertised:</p><p> </p><ul><li>Established reputation as a leader in the field of charity law</li><li>A strong understanding of high risk, high impact or novel legal issues within the charitable sector</li><li>Knowledge of the Commission’s regulatory powers and how it can best fulfil its statutory objectives throughout its operation</li><li>Strong intellectual and analytical ability</li><li>A commitment to and understanding of the charity sector’s effective, independent, proportionate, and impartial regulation</li><li>Personal integrity, demonstrable independence and attitudes consistent with the expectations of senior public office.</li></ul><p> </p><p> </p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820759/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-19T13:36:49.547Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820759/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820759/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-01-11","Charity Commission: Public Appointments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what the selection criteria were for the most recent round of appointments to the board of the Charities Commission.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","122177"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820760","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-01-19","<p>Eleven individuals applied for the Charity Commission Legal Trustee role, which was advertised in the most recent round of appointments to the board of the Charity Commission.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820760/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-19T13:38:24.037Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820760/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820760/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-01-11","Charity Commission: Public Appointments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, how many people applied for positions in the most recent round of appointments to the board of the Charity Commission.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","122178"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820761","Cabinet Office","false","2018-01-17","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820761/answer","PQ122179 Jon Trickett(OW) .pdf","PQ122179 Jon Trickett(OW) .pdf","UKSA Response ","UKSA Response ",,"2018-01-17T13:59:56.657Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820761/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820761/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-01-11","Learning Disability: Hemsworth","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what proportion of adults with a learning disability in Hemsworth constituency were in paid work in (a) 2015, (b) 2016 and (c) 2017.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","122179"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820762","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-01-16","<p>There are no plans to assess poverty levels in connection with closures of individual sites such as Tile Hill Jobcentre.</p><p> </p><p>I would stress that the office mergers are not about reducing services but about taking the opportunity to stop spending money on empty space so we can spend more on supporting those in need. The face-to-face support our work coaches offer at jobcentres will continue to be a core part of the service we deliver.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>National statistics on the number of individuals in relative low income are set out in DWP’s annual ‘Households Below Average Income’ publication. Latest 3-year estimates for the West Midlands region in 2013/14 - 2015/16 show the rate of individuals in low income households at 19%, before housing costs.</p><p> </p><p>The number and proportion of individuals in relative low income is not available at a local authority or constituency level because the survey sample sizes are too small to support the production of robust estimates at this geography. Estimates to 2016/17 have been pre-announced to be published in March 2018.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820762/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-16T12:00:42.027Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820762/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820762/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-01-11","Jobcentres: Coventry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if she will make an assessment of the potential effect of the closure of Tile Hill jobcentre on levels of poverty in the area served by that jobcentre.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","122180"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820763","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-01-19","<p>UK zoos are already required to have robust controls in place to make sure that all animals in their collections can be properly accounted for. A zoo needs a licence from its local authority to operate and will be inspected before a licence is issued and periodically thereafter. Zoos are required to maintain robust records of individual animals in their collection and to make these available to zoo inspectors. Records include details of the date an animal entered the collection, how it was disposed of and, where relevant, to whom.</p><p> </p><p>The Secretariat to the Convention on International Trade in Endangered Species (CITES) has requested that Parties report progress on implementing this decision to the 70<sup>th</sup> CITES Standing Committee to be held in October this year.</p><p> </p><p><strong><br> </strong></p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820763/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-19T12:58:30.133Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820763/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820763/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-01-11","Convention on International Trade in Endangered Species","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps his Department has taken to implement Decision 17.226 of the Convention on International Trade in Endangered Species of Wild Fauna and Flora in the UK.","false","Biography information for Kerry McCarthy","Bristol East","Kerry McCarthy","122181"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820764","Department for Education","false","2018-01-16","<p>The department collects data on the weekly cost of childcare through our regular parent surveys. These can be found at the following link: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/statistics-childcare-and-early-years" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/statistics-childcare-and-early-years</a>.</p><p><strong><br> </strong></p><p> </p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820764/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-16T17:36:52.06Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820764/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820764/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-01-11","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the average weekly cost was of a childcare place in the West Midlands in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","122182"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820765","Attorney General","false","2018-01-16","<p>The SFO criminal investigation into G4S and Serco electronic monitoring contracts is still ongoing. SFO cases are by their very nature complex, lengthy and resource intensive and it is not unusual for them to take a considerable time to be concluded. However, the SFO will publish information about this case on its website when it is appropriate to do so.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820765/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-16T16:19:33.367Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820765/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820765/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2018-01-11","Electronic Tagging","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, when the Serious Fraud Office investigation into the G4S and Serco electronic monitoring contracts which was initiated in 2013 is due to conclude.","false","Biography information for Afzal Khan","Manchester, Gorton","Afzal Khan","122183"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820766","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-01-16","<p>The Joint Report issued by the UK and EU negotiating teams on 8 December was clear that UK entities would be able to continue to participate in all EU programmes, including the space programmes, financed by the current Multiannual Financial Framework, which ends in 2020. Clearly there will be further discussions on exactly what this means for the individual programmes during Phase 2 of negotiations, but the principle set out in the report is that eligibility of entities located in the UK will be unaffected by the UK’s withdrawal from the EU.</p><p> </p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820766/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-16T14:36:59.567Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820766/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820766/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-01-11","Global Navigation Satellite Systems","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether the UK leaving the EU will affect the contracts to produce the payloads for the European Union Global Navigation satellite system in the UK.","false","Biography information for Dr Philippa Whitford","Central Ayrshire","Dr Philippa Whitford","122184"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820767","Department for International Development","false","2018-01-18","<p>UK funding contributes to the salaries of individual vetted health and education Palestinian Authority (PA) public servants on the EU Palestinian-European Socio-Economic Management Assistance Mechanism (PEGASE) list, including PA teachers in the West Bank. It is the PA’s responsibility to deploy these vetted public servants to schools in the West Bank as they see fit. UK funding enables around 25,000 young Palestinians to receive an education annually. The UK government strongly condemns all forms of violence and hatred. Our partnership with the Palestinian Authority includes a commitment from the Palestinian leadership to adhere to the principle of non-violence and to tackle language and actions that could incite violence or hatred.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820767/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-18T17:23:40.71Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820767/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820767/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-01-11","Palestinians: Teachers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, pursuant to the Answer of 8 January 2018 to Question 120545, whether the Government provides funding for the salaries of teachers at (a) the Dalal Mughrabi Elementary School in Beit Awwa, near Hebron, (b) the Dalal Mughrabi Elementary School for Girls in Al-Shuyoukh, Hebron, (c) the Dalal Mughrabi High School for Girls in Al-Shuyoukh, Hebron or (d) the Dalal Mughrabi Elementary School for Boys and Girls, Jenin.","false","Biography information for Andrew Percy","Brigg and Goole","Andrew Percy","122185"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820768","HM Treasury","false","2018-01-16","<p>HMRC publishes reports on the estimated cost of the various tax reliefs. Information on the Income Tax relief for investments in Venture Capital Trusts, the Enterprise Investment Scheme and Seed Investment Enterprise Scheme, and Capital Gains Tax relief for the Enterprise Investment Scheme can be found in:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/main-tax-expenditures-and-structural-reliefs" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/main-tax-expenditures-and-structural-reliefs</a></p><p> </p><p>Information on the Capital Gains Tax relief for investments in Venture Capital Trusts and the Seed Enterprise Investment Scheme can be found in:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/minor-tax-expenditures-and-structural-reliefs" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/minor-tax-expenditures-and-structural-reliefs</a></p><p> </p><p>These tables include the information back to 2012-13.</p><p> </p><p>Combined IT and CGT relief for years prior to this can be found in:</p><p><a href="http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20120207135500/http:/www.hmrc.gov.uk/stats/tax_expenditures/menu.htm" target="_blank">http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20120207135500/http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/stats/tax_expenditures/menu.htm</a></p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820768/answer",,,,,"122187","2018-01-16T17:36:19.047Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820768/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820768/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-01-11","Venture Capital: Tax Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the cost to the public purse was of venture capital schemes: tax relief for investors in (a) 2010, (b) 2011, (c) 2012, (d) 2013, (e) 2014, (f) 2015, (g) 2016 and (h) 2017.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","122186"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820769","HM Treasury","false","2018-01-16","<p>HMRC publishes reports on the estimated cost of the various tax reliefs. Information on the Income Tax relief for investments in Venture Capital Trusts, the Enterprise Investment Scheme and Seed Investment Enterprise Scheme, and Capital Gains Tax relief for the Enterprise Investment Scheme can be found in:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/main-tax-expenditures-and-structural-reliefs" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/main-tax-expenditures-and-structural-reliefs</a></p><p> </p><p>Information on the Capital Gains Tax relief for investments in Venture Capital Trusts and the Seed Enterprise Investment Scheme can be found in:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/minor-tax-expenditures-and-structural-reliefs" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/minor-tax-expenditures-and-structural-reliefs</a></p><p> </p><p>These tables include the information back to 2012-13.</p><p> </p><p>Combined IT and CGT relief for years prior to this can be found in:</p><p><a href="http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20120207135500/http:/www.hmrc.gov.uk/stats/tax_expenditures/menu.htm" target="_blank">http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20120207135500/http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/stats/tax_expenditures/menu.htm</a></p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820769/answer",,,,,"122186","2018-01-16T17:36:19.093Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820769/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820769/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-01-11","Enterprise Investment Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the cost to the public purse was of the enterprise investment scheme in (a) 2010, (b) 2011, (c) 2012, (d) 2013, (e) 2014, (f) 2015, (g) 2016 and (h) 2017.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","122187"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820770","HM Treasury","false","2018-01-19","<p>The estimated impact of the 50p rate of tax was set out in the HM Revenue and Customs report “The Exchequer effect of the 50 per cent additional rate of income tax”:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20140206181159/http:/www.hmrc.gov.uk/budget2012/excheq-income-tax-2042.pdf" target="_blank">http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20140206181159/http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/budget2012/excheq-income-tax-2042.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>This report showed that the 50p rate was a distortive and economically inefficient way of raising revenue and it did not raise what was expected. It raised at best only £1 billion and at worst could have cost the Exchequer. This is considerably less than the £2.5bn which was expected when introduced by Labour.</p><p> </p><p>There has been no new evidence to suggest the conclusions of this report were incorrect.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820770/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-19T12:44:31.79Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820770/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820770/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-01-11","Income Tax: Tax Rates and Bands","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment his Department has made of the potential merits of abolishing the 50p income tax rate.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","122188"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820771","Department for International Trade","false","2018-01-17","<p>We have made public a summary of the responses we received which was published on 5 January. Views are not attributed to individual respondents or groups of respondents. We have summarised the responses and some organisations have made their own responses public. For those that haven’t we are treating their response as confidential.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820771/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-17T12:26:31.797Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820771/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820771/answer","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820771/answer/previousversion/34686","Biography information for Greg Hands","202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-01-11","Trade Agreements","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, pursuant to the Answer of 9 January 2018 to Question 120867, on Trade Agreements, for what reason that answer does not contain the list of organisations which submitted responses.","false","Biography information for Bill Esterson","Sefton Central","Bill Esterson","122189"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820772","HM Treasury","false","2018-01-16","<p>The National Insurance Fund (NIF) is used to pay for contributory benefits, including the State Pension. The NIF has no borrowing powers, so maintains a working balance of at least 16.6% of projected benefit expenditure to ensure that the NIF can deal with short term fluctuations. Information on the historical NIF receipts and balance is available in the National Insurance Fund Accounts at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/national-insurance-fund-accounts" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/national-insurance-fund-accounts</a></p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820772/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-16T12:02:12.28Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820772/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820772/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-01-11","State Retirement Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the size of the state pension fund was in (a) 2010, (b) 2011, (c) 2012, (d) 2013, (e) 2014, (f) 2015, (g) 2016 and (h) 2017.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","122190"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820773","Home Office","false","2018-01-16","<p>We are reviewing the regulation of air weapons in England and Wales, and we have asked for the views of interested parties by 6 February 2018.</p><p>The review is looking at issues such as manufacturing standards, secure storage and whether current arrangements are sufficient to prevent children gaining access to air weapons. We will also take account of the arrangements in Scotland and Northern Ireland where air weapons are subject to a licensing regime. We will publish the outcome of the review in due course.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick  Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820773/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-16T11:34:51.403Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820773/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820773/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-01-11","Airguns: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether her Department plans to introduce air gun licensing.","false","Biography information for Luke Pollard","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Luke Pollard","122191"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820774","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-01-17","<p>The administration and payment of survivor benefits in occupational pension schemes is the responsibility of individual pension schemes and is not a matter for government.</p>","Hexham","Guy Opperman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820774/answer",,,,,"122193 ; 122194","2018-01-17T11:51:37.107Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820774/answer","Biography information for Guy Opperman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820774/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-01-11","Occupational Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment she has made of the effectiveness of safeguards to ensure pensions are inherited to the intended recipient.","false","Biography information for Chris Elmore","Ogmore","Chris Elmore","122192"
