"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820857","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-01-23","<p>The Government is working with all of the combined authorities to support ambitious and innovative plans for new homes, and a more strategic approach to planning for homes and infrastructure. Specific housing investment measures have also been agreed already as part of devolution deals with the mayoral combined authorities in Greater Manchester and Cambridgeshire &amp; Peterborough.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820857/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-23T13:22:26.003Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820857/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820857/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-01-11","Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, whether his Department is working with combined authorities in delivering new housing schemes.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","122275"
