"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820859","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-01-16","<p>We received a number of submissions to the Channel 4 regional consultation from individuals and local authorities across the UK. No decisions have been taken. The government is working with Channel 4 on how it can best increase its regional impact, and we will set out next steps in due course.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820859/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-16T14:30:30.023Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820859/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820859/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-01-11","Channel Four Television: Location","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment his Department has made of the benefits to the West Midlands economy of Channel 4 relocating to Wolverhampton; what his policy is on the location of Channel 4; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Emma Reynolds","Wolverhampton North East","Emma Reynolds","122277"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820860","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-01-22","<p>The cost of combined authorities’ functions is met by their constituent local authorities. In addition, the government is backing all six city region mayors and their combined authorities with a targeted capacity fund, worth £6 million per year across the six areas for the next two years, to help them deliver their priorities.</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820860/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-22T16:30:34.527Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820860/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820860/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-01-11","Combined Authorities","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what the cost to the public purse for each combined authority in each year since those authorities were established has been.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","122278"
