"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820942","Home Office","false","2018-01-16","<p>On 26 October 2017 the Government announced its plans for reform of the National Referral Mechanism (NRM) confirming the Government’s commitment to markedly improving the identification of, and support provided to, victims of modern slavery. This includes incorporating the Human Trafficking Foundation Trafficking Survivor Care Standards as a minimum standard of victim support that will be incorporated into in all future Government adult victim support contracts.</p><p><br> Detailed implementation plans for the whole reform programme are currently being developed, and further information will be announced in due course.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820942/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-16T17:56:11.097Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820942/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820942/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-01-11","Slavery","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the oral contribution of the Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State of 26 October 2017, Official Report, column 512, when the Government plans officially to adopt the Human Trafficking Foundation's trafficking survivor care standards as a minimum standard for victim support.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","122360"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820943","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-01-19","<p>The Department for Exiting the European Union is undertaking a comprehensive programme of analytical work across a range of scenarios. We are examining all areas of the UK economy from a number of perspectives and seeking input from a wide range of stakeholders. As part of this, we have looked at 58 sectors of the economy, as set out in our response to the Lords EU External Affairs Sub-committee report “Brexit: Trade in Goods” which can be found at: <a href="https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld201617/ldselect/ldeucom/129/129.pdf" target="_blank">https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld201617/ldselect/ldeucom/129/129.pdf</a>.</p><p> </p><p>We will continue to engage with businesses and industry bodies from all sectors of the economy, and all regions and nations of the UK, in order to inform our negotiations with the EU.</p><p> </p><p>We have published 14 detailed papers on the negotiations to date and will continue to be as open as possible subject to the overwhelming national interest of preserving our negotiating position. Ministers have a specific responsibility, which Parliament has endorsed, not to release information that would undermine our negotiating position.</p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820943/answer","Brexit- trade in goods.pdf","Brexit- trade in goods.pdf","Brexit: Trade in Goods","Brexit: Trade in Goods","122058 ; 122059 ; 122352 ; 122490 ; 123126 ; 123129","2018-01-19T16:18:35.883Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820943/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820943/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-01-11","Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what information his Department plans to publish on the effect of the UK leaving the EU on different sectors of the economy in addition to that information released by his Department on 27 November 2017 before any Parliamentary vote on (a) the UK's withdrawal agreement or (b) a UK-EU trade deal.","false","Biography information for Jo Platt","Leigh","Jo Platt","122361"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820944","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-01-19","<p>We have had no such discussions. The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) assessed the cost benefit of Orkambi and was unable to recommend it. Vertex has been encouraged to engage in negotiations with NHS England and if it comes forward with a new proposal, NICE will be able to reconsider.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820944/answer",,,,,"122370 ; 122372 ; 122374","2018-01-19T11:36:20.11Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820944/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820944/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-01-11","Orkambi: Germany","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, whether he has discussed with his German counterpart the cost-effectiveness of Orkambi in that country's health service treatment of cystic fibrosis.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","122362"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820945","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-01-17","<p>The Government has close and regular dialogue with the US Administration on all aspects of nuclear and arms control policy. In early 2017, President Trump announced that the US would conduct a Nuclear Posture Review. The US has sought views from the UK and other Allies as part of the process. The Review has not yet been concluded.</p>","South Staffordshire","Gavin Williamson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820945/answer",,,,,"122320","2018-01-17T15:21:29.043Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820945/answer","Biography information for Gavin Williamson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820945/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-01-11","USA: Nuclear Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what discussions he has had with his US counterpart on the that country's latest Nuclear Posture Review; and what implications that review has for the UK's nuclear defence policy.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","122363"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820946","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-01-17","<p>This Government remains fully committed to maintaining the UK's minimum, credible, independent nuclear deterrent. We continue to assess developments in the international security environment and remain confident we have the right balance of nuclear capability to deter the most extreme threats to the UK and our allies.</p>","South Staffordshire","Gavin Williamson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820946/answer",,,,,"122324","2018-01-17T15:20:32.747Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820946/answer","Biography information for Gavin Williamson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820946/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-01-11","Nuclear Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what recent assessment his Department has made of the strategic relevance of the deployment of low-yield nuclear warheads.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","122364"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820947","Home Office","false","2018-01-16","<p>On 26 October 2017 the Government announced its plans for reform of the National Referral Mechanism (NRM) confirming the Government’s commitment to markedly improving the identification of, and support provided to, victims of modern slavery. This includes strengthening the role of designated first responders by considering who should be a first responder and how they should be trained, and introducing a new digital system for referrals and case working. We are currently running a procurement exercise for the digital solution and the timetable for building and implementation of the system is dependent on commercial processes.</p><p>Detailed implementation plans for the whole reform programme are currently being developed and further information will be announced in due course.</p><p> </p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820947/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-16T17:56:35.047Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820947/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820947/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-01-11","Slavery","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the oral contribution of the Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State of 27 October 2017, Official Report, col. 512, when the new digital system will be developed to support the National Referral Mechanism process to make it easier for people on the front line to refer victims for support.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","122365"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820948","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-01-19","<p>Responses have now been sent.</p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820948/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-19T13:58:11.6Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820948/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820948/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-01-11","Members: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, when he plans to respond to the two letters from the hon. Member for West Lancashire dated 13 October 2017.","false","Biography information for Rosie Cooper","West Lancashire","Rosie Cooper","122366"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820949","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-01-17","<p>The Government has close and regular dialogue with the US Administration on all aspects of nuclear and arms control policy. On 20 December 2017, we published the report 'The United Kingdom's Future Nuclear Deterrent: The Dreadnought Programme, 2017 Update to Parliament', which includes aspects of our work with the US on maintaining the Trident D5 II missile and associated UK warhead.</p>","South Staffordshire","Gavin Williamson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820949/answer","20171220_WMS_Future_Nuclear_Deterrent.docx","20171220_WMS_Future_Nuclear_Deterrent.docx","HCWS377 - Future Nuclear Deterrent 2017 Update","HCWS377 - Future Nuclear Deterrent 2017 Update","122326","2018-01-17T15:18:15.14Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820949/answer","Biography information for Gavin Williamson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820949/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-01-11","USA: Trident Missiles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether he has had any discussions with his US counterpart on the development of a modified version of the Trident D5 submarine-launched missiles; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","122367"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820950","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-01-17","<p>As set out in the 2015 Strategic Defence and Security Review, we continue to keep our nuclear posture under constant review in the light of the international security environment and the actions of potential adversaries. We remain deliberately ambiguous about precisely when, how and at what scale we would contemplate use of our nuclear weapons, in order not to simplify the calculations of any potential aggressor and in order to protect our national security.</p>","South Staffordshire","Gavin Williamson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820950/answer",,,,,"122327","2018-01-17T15:22:05.997Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820950/answer","Biography information for Gavin Williamson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820950/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-01-11","Nuclear Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the Government’s policy is on the use of nuclear weapons in retaliation to non-nuclear strategic attacks.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","122368"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820951","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-01-17","<p>Any decisions on UK nuclear deterrence policy or capability will be fully compliant with our obligations under the Nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty.</p>","South Staffordshire","Gavin Williamson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820951/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-17T15:19:36.36Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820951/answer","Biography information for Gavin Williamson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820951/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-01-11","Nuclear Weapons: Proliferation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the compatibility of the development of new nuclear weapons with the Government's policy on non-proliferation.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","122369"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820952","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-01-19","<p>We have had no such discussions. The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) assessed the cost benefit of Orkambi and was unable to recommend it. Vertex has been encouraged to engage in negotiations with NHS England and if it comes forward with a new proposal, NICE will be able to reconsider.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820952/answer",,,,,"122362 ; 122372 ; 122374","2018-01-19T11:36:20.173Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820952/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820952/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-01-11","Orkambi: Austria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, whether he has had recent discussions with his Austrian counterpart on the cost-effectiveness of Orkambi in treating cystic fibrosis.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","122370"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820953","Department for Transport","false","2018-01-17","<p>The Department makes long-term projections of rail demand and revenues, for planning and budgeting purposes, and to assess the case for enhancement schemes. These take into account a range of factors.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820953/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-17T13:13:27.253Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820953/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820953/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-01-11","Railways: Fares","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment his Department has made of the effect of the rail fare rises implemented in January 2018 on rail (a) patronage and (b) revenues.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","122371"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820954","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-01-19","<p>We have had no such discussions. The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) assessed the cost benefit of Orkambi and was unable to recommend it. Vertex has been encouraged to engage in negotiations with NHS England and if it comes forward with a new proposal, NICE will be able to reconsider.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820954/answer",,,,,"122362 ; 122370 ; 122374","2018-01-19T11:36:20.22Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820954/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820954/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-01-11","Orkambi: Denmark","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, whether he has had recent discussions with his Danish counterpart on the cost-effectiveness of Orkambi in treating cystic fibrosis.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","122372"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820955","Home Office","false","2018-01-16","<p>On 26 October 2017 the Government announced its plans for reform of the National Referral Mechanism (NRM) confirming the Government’s commitment to markedly improving the identification of, and support provided to, victims of modern slavery. This includes the laying of regulations to enshrine the rights of victims in law, and the development of statutory guidance under s49 of the Modern Slavery Act 2015.</p><p>Detailed implementation plans for the reform programme are currently being developed, including the process for consulting on the statutory guidance, and further information will be announced in due course.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820955/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-16T17:55:52.47Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820955/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820955/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-01-11","Slavery","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, with reference to the oral contribution of The Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for the Home Department of 26 October 2017, Official Report, col. 512, when she plans to initiate the consultation on the preparation of statutory guidance under s48 of the Modern Slavery Act 2015 on the identification of and support for victims of modern slavery; what the terms of reference for that consultation will be; and between what dates that consultation will run.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","122373"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820956","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-01-19","<p>We have had no such discussions. The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) assessed the cost benefit of Orkambi and was unable to recommend it. Vertex has been encouraged to engage in negotiations with NHS England and if it comes forward with a new proposal, NICE will be able to reconsider.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820956/answer",,,,,"122362 ; 122370 ; 122372","2018-01-19T11:36:20.25Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820956/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820956/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-01-11","Orkambi: France","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health of Social Care, whether he has had recent discussions with his French counterpart on the cost-effectiveness of Orkambi in treating cystic fibrosis.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","122374"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820957","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-01-19","<p>The Department for Exiting the European Union is working with all departments at both ministerial and official level to make sure that our preparations for our exit from and new partnership with the EU are on track. The Secretary of State continues to have regular conversations with Cabinet colleagues on all aspects of exiting the EU.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820957/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-19T16:21:57.88Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820957/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820957/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-01-11","Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what recent discussions he has had with Cabinet colleagues on conducting market access assessments for when the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Jo Platt","Leigh","Jo Platt","122375"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820958","Department for Transport","false","2018-01-16","<p>As the chancellor announced at Autumn Budget, half of the Transforming Cities Fund has been allocated to the Mayoral Combined Authorities on a per capita basis to allow mayors to take decisions on their transport priorities.</p><p> </p><p>The remainder of the fund will be awarded to other major cities outside London via a competitive process. The details of this process will be announced shortly.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820958/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-16T14:59:56.497Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820958/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820958/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-01-11","Transforming Cities Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that cities which do not have a metro mayor receive an appropriate allocation from the Transforming Cities Fund.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","122376"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820959","HM Treasury","false","2018-01-16","<p>More than 170,000 parents have a Tax-Free Childcare account. Over 45,000 parents have made a payment from their account. Many of the parents with a Tax-Free Childcare account are accessing 30 hours free childcare, meaning they have not yet needed to use Tax-Free Childcare. The childcare service is being gradually rolled out to parents of older children and therefore we expect usage to increase over time.</p><p> </p><p>The average annual operating cost for the childcare service (through which parents access 30 hours free childcare and/or Tax-Free Childcare) over the five years to 2021/22 is estimated as £35.5m. The average annual operating cost for the Childcare Choices site is £8,800.</p><p> </p><p>All remaining parents will be able to access Tax-Free Childcare by 14 February. When fully rolled out we estimate that 1.2 million families would be better off under Tax-Free Childcare.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820959/answer",,,,,"122378 ; 122379","2018-01-16T12:01:19.663Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820959/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820959/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-01-11","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many (a) parents and (b) families (i) have registered for and (ii) are receiving payments through the tax free childcare scheme.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","122377"
