0,313</p></td><td><p>6,007</p></td><td><p>109,793,233</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Notes:</p><ol><li>Defence costs include profit, costs and disbursements such as counsel, expert fees and court fees. It would not be correct to say that these are the sums received by those firms for the services that they alone provide.</li></ol><p> </p><ol start="2"><li>The variability in the numbers for the firms is caused by the number of offices the defence firm has on the panel.</li></ol><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819906/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-15T17:03:48.847Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819906/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819906/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-01-10","NHS: Negligence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, if he will list the solicitors instructed to defend clinical negligence claims against the NHS where the claim has resolved, and for each such firm (a) what fees were paid, (b) how many claims were made and (c) how many of those were successful as denoted by payment of damages whether by court award or settlement in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Mr John Baron","Basildon and Billericay","Mr John Baron","121978"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819907","Home Office","false","2018-01-17","<p>We have a proud history of providing protection to those who need it, for as long as it is needed, in accordance with our international obligations under the Refugee Convention. However, refugee status is not necessarily permanent and it may be appropriate to revoke such status where it is clear someone no longer needs protection; where evidence emerges that status was obtained by deception; or where someone commits a serious crime and is a danger to the community or represents a threat to national security.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline  Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819907/answer",,,,,"121980","2018-01-17T12:57:14.057Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819907/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819907/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-01-10","Asylum","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many cessation of international protection (Articles 11 and 17 Directive 2011/95/EU) decisions were made by the UK in response to asylum applications in 2017; and how many cessation of international protection decisions were made by the UK in 2017 by nationality of applicant.","false","Biography information for Mohammad Yasin","Bedford","Mohammad Yasin","121979"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819908","Home Office","false","2018-01-17","<p>We have a proud history of providing protection to those who need it, for as long as it is needed, in accordance with our international obligations under the Refugee Convention. However, refugee status is not necessarily permanent and it may be appropriate to revoke such status where it is clear someone no longer needs protection; where evidence emerges that status was obtained by deception; or where someone commits a serious crime and is a danger to the community or represents a threat to national security.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline  Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819908/answer",,,,,"121979","2018-01-17T12:57:14.107Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819908/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819908/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-01-10","Asylum","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many withdrawal of international protection (Articles 14 and 19 Directive 2011/95/EU) decisions were made by the UK in response to asylum applications in 2017; and how many withdrawal of international protection decisions were made by the UK in 2017 by nationality of applicant.","false","Biography information for Mohammad Yasin","Bedford","Mohammad Yasin","121980"
